%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russia-Ukraine%20War%3A%20Starlink%20Row%20Offers%20a%20Cautionary%20Tale%20on%20Role%20of%20Private%20Space%20Industry%20in%20Wars%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F16183940%2FEffect-2024-02-16T183909.210.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20ongoing%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%2C%20the%20role%20of%20the%20United%20States%E2%80%99%20aerospace%20agency%20SpaceX%20has%20become%20very%20prominent.%20In%20February%202022%2C%20Ukrainian%20authorities%20requested%20support%20from%20SpaceX%2C%20mainly%20for%20space-based%20internet%20services.%20In%20response%2C%20they%20were%20provided%20with%20Starlink%20satellite%20internet%20service%20as%20the%20war%20destroyed%20the%20existing%20network.%20Today%2C%20Starlink%20is%20being%20used%20by%20civilians%20as%20well%20as%20the%20military%20in%20Ukraine.%20Also%2C%20possibly%20Ukraine%20could%20be%20getting%20high-resolution%20satellite%20imagery%20from%20companies%20like%20Maxar%20and%20Planet%20Labs%20(assistance%20form%20CubeSats).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20present%2C%20after%20using%20these%20services%20for%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20claimed%20that%20the%20Russian%20forces%20are%20using%20Starlink%20services%20in%20occupied%20areas.%20The%20problem%20appears%20to%20be%20more%20%E2%80%98systemic%E2%80%99.%20Starlink%20has%20claimed%20that%20it%20has%20no%20links%20with%20Russia.%20However%2C%20there%20is%20a%20possibility%20that%20Russian%20forces%20in%20occupied%20areas%20of%20Ukraine%20could%20be%20using%20Starlink%20terminals%20provided%20by%20SpaceX%2C%20or%20may%20have%20used%20them%20during%20the%20early%20phases%20of%20the%20war%20for%20the%20purposes%20of%20satellite%20internet%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2024%2Ffeb%2F12%2Fukraine-accuses-russia-forces-using-elon-musk-starlink%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSpaceX%2520does%2520not%2520do%2520business%2Cequipment%2520to%2520locations%2520in%2520Russia%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20claim%20that%20terminals%20are%20being%20used%20by%20units%20like%20Russia%E2%80%99s%2083rd%20air%20assault%20brigade%20in%20the%20partially%20occupied%20eastern%20region%20of%20Donetsk.%20Technically%2C%20Starlink%20terminals%20should%20be%20%E2%80%98geofenced%E2%80%99%20to%20restrict%20any%20operations%20from%20unauthorised%20locations.%20Knowing%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20skills%20in%20the%20cyber%20offensive%20domain%2C%20it%20could%20be%20possible%20for%20them%20to%20%E2%80%98spoof%E2%80%99%20the%20geofence%20to%20make%20a%20terminal%20in%20a%20blocked%20area%20appear%20as%20if%20it%20is%20in%20a%20permitted%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERole%20of%20private%20space%20players%20in%20wars%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20the%20private%20space%20industry%20coming%20to%20the%20assistance%20of%20a%20state%20during%20a%20war%20is%20not%20new.%20During%20the%201991%20Gulf%20War%2C%20Iraq%20had%20access%20to%20the%20French%20SPOT%20commercial%20imager.%20Much%20before%20the%20war%2C%20the%20French%20agency%20had%20some%20commercial%20agreements%20with%20Iraq.%20The%20US%20used%20diplomatic%20channels%20and%20a%20UN-mandated%20embargo%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapps.dtic.mil%2Fsti%2Ftr%2Fpdf%2FADA400933.pdf%5C%22%3Esatellite%20imagery%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20stop%20the%20sales%20to%20Iraq%2C%20allowing%20the%20US%20and%20allied%20forces%20to%20have%20a%20monopoly%20on%20satellite%20imagery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20reported%20that%20during%20September%202022%20Ukrainian%20forces%20had%20planned%20an%20attack%20on%20the%20Russian%20naval%20fleet%20based%20at%20Sevastopol%20in%20Crimea.%20They%20had%20six%20lethal%20drone%20systems%20ready%20for%20this%20purpose.%20However%2C%20these%20systems%20could%20not%20get%20any%20support%20from%20Starlink%2C%20the%20satellite%20communications%20system.%20This%20system%20was%20not%20operative%20in%20this%20region%2C%20and%20as%20per%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20since%20he%20was%20not%20keen%20to%20expand%20the%20war%20towards%20Crimea%2C%20he%20refused%20any%20assistance.%20As%20per%20him%2C%20he%20had%20a%20discussion%20with%20the%20Russian%20ambassador%20to%20the%20United%20States%20and%20was%20warned%20that%20any%20escalation%20of%20the%20war%20to%20the%20Russian-occupied%20Crimea%20area%20would%20lead%20to%20a%20nuclear%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20this%20gives%20us%20some%20glimpses%20into%20what%20role%20the%20private%20space%20industry%20(and%20their%20owners)%20could%20play%20in%20future%20wars%20in%20deciding%20their%20outcomes.%20Elon%20Musk%20is%20known%20as%20an%20inspiring%20and%20visionary%20entrepreneur.%20But%2C%20he%20is%20also%20known%20as%20a%20person%20with%20multiple%20moods%20and%20modes.%20In%20the%20current%20context%2C%20it%20is%20he%20who%20has%20decided%20to%20avoid%20any%20possible%20entry%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%20into%20the%20conflict.%20The%20decision%20taken%20by%20him%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20humanity%20should%20be%20welcomed.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20not%20about%20any%20particular%20individual%2C%20but%20the%20idea%20itself%20that%20such%20a%20decision%20was%20taken%20by%20a%20private%20individual%20is%20itself%20very%20frightening.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F16184737%2FSteve_Jurvetson_with_Starlink_user_terminal.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F16184737%2FSteve_Jurvetson_with_Starlink_user_terminal.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F16184737%2FSteve_Jurvetson_with_Starlink_user_terminal-300x293.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F16184737%2FSteve_Jurvetson_with_Starlink_user_terminal-1024x1001.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697566%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221173%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESpaceX%20board%20member%20Steve%20Jurvetson%20holding%20a%20Starlink%20user%20terminal%20in%20June%202020.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FSteve%20Jurvetson%2FCC%20BY%202.0%20DEED%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHistory%20tells%20us%20that%20during%20conventional%20wars%2C%20winning%20sides%20use%20captured%20weapons%20and%20equipment%20as%20war%20trophies.%20Mainly%2C%20guerrilla%20forces%20are%20interested%20in%20capturing%20the%20weapons%20and%20equipment%20of%20enemies%20for%20reuse.%20Today%2C%20the%20situation%20is%20a%20bit%20different%2C%20and%20in%20an%20unfinished%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20Russia%20is%20using%20the%20assets%20of%20SpaceX%20available%20on%20the%20ground.%20%C2%A0There%20is%20a%20possibility%20that%20if%20some%20Ukraine%20state%20assets%20were%20available%20in%20occupied%20areas%2C%20Russian%20forces%20could%20have%20used%20them%20also.%20However%2C%20the%20broader%20question%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20asked%20at%20this%20point%20is%20if%20the%20private%20space%20industry%20decides%20arbitrarily%20about%20which%20actor%20involved%20in%20war%20should%20be%20given%20access%20to%20their%20facilities.%20From%20the%201991%20Gulf%20War%20to%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20space%20technology%20has%20evolved%20and%20so%20is%20the%20case%20with%20the%20private%20space%20industry.%20Against%20this%20backdrop%2C%20there%20is%20a%20need%20for%20some%20introspection%20about%20the%20role%20of%20the%20space%20industry%20in%20security%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20reality%20that%20the%20private%20space%20industry%20is%20here%20to%20earn%20profits%20and%20there%20is%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20this.%20It%20would%20sustain%20provided%20it%20earns%20profits.%20It%20is%20important%20to%20have%20some%20mechanism%20of%20checks%20and%20balances%20in%20regard%20to%20the%20role%20of%20private%20space%20players%20in%20security%20matters.%20Initially%2C%20SpaceX%20had%20decided%20to%20offer%20the%20services%20to%20Ukraine%20free%20of%20cost.%20%C2%A0Subsequently%2C%20the%20US%20defence%20establishment%20has%20got%20into%20an%20official%20contract%20with%20Starlink%20in%20this%20regard.%20The%20exact%20details%20of%20this%20contract%20are%20not%20known.%20There%20is%20a%20possibility%20that%20any%20space%20industry%20in%20a%20driver%E2%80%99s%20seat%20could%20look%20after%20their%20own%20interests%20than%20to%20bother%20much%20about%20the%20geostrategic%20consequences%20of%20their%20actions.%20Also%2C%20there%20is%20a%20possibility%20of%20the%20private%20space%20industry%20going%20%E2%80%98rouge%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAny%20proliferation%20of%20high-resolution%20commercial%20satellite%20imagery%20holds%20a%20possible%20danger.%20There%20is%20a%20possibility%20that%20the%20private%20space%20agency%20would%20not%20even%20come%20to%20know%20about%20the%20actual%20intent%20of%20its%20customers%20behind%20acquiring%20such%20information.%20Today%2C%20states%20are%20found%20keen%20to%20outsource%20various%20satellite-based%20services%20from%20remote%20sensing%20to%20commutations%20to%20private%20space%20agencies.%20Obviously%2C%20during%20wars%20(even%20otherwise)%20states%20would%20be%20required%20to%20depend%20much%20on%20the%20private%20space%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20agencies%20like%20SpaceX%20are%20capable%20of%20manipulating%20geopolitics%2C%20if%20they%20desire%20to%20do%20so.%20Owing%20to%20the%20increasing%20government%20encouragement%2C%20more%20private%20actors%20like%20SpaceX%20are%20likely%20to%20emerge%20in%20the%20future.%20During%20the%20recent%20much%20talked%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DhYfByTcY49k%5C%22%3ETucker%20Carlson%E2%80%99s%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%2C%20there%20is%20a%20mention%20that%20Elon%20Musk%20has%20already%20had%20a%20chip%20implanted%20in%20the%20human%20brain%20and%20in%20future%20states%20would%20be%20required%20to%20deal%20with%20private%20actors%20like%20him%20to%20ensure%20no%20misuse%20of%20technology%20happens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObviously%2C%20critical%20technologies%20in%20private%20hands%2C%20be%20it%20space%20technology%20or%20any%20other%20emerging%20technology%2C%20there%20always%20would%20be%20some%20associated%20security%20challenges.%20The%20issue%20of%20the%20use%20of%20private%20space%20players%20in%20the%20business%20of%20warfare%20needs%20a%20critical%20assessment.%20Encouraging%20private%20industry%20is%20important%20for%20the%20growth%20but%20at%20the%20same%20time%20the%20history%20of%20East%20India%20Company%20should%20not%20be%20forgotten.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAjey%20Lele%20researches%20space%20issues%20and%20is%20the%20author%20of%20the%20book%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EInstitutions%20That%20Shaped%20Modern%20India%3A%20ISRO%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708091126000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F16183940%2FEffect-2024-02-16T183909.210.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Frussia-ukraine-war-starlink-row-offers-a-cautionary-tale-on-role-of-private-space-industry-in-wars%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20controversy%20emerged%20after%20Ukraine%20claimed%20that%20the%20Russian%20forces%20are%20using%20Starlink%20internet%20services%20in%20occupied%20areas.%20Despite%20Space%20X%20claiming%20that%20it%20has%20no%20links%20with%20Russia%2C%20the%20controversy%20refuses%20to%20die%20down.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Frussia-ukraine-war-starlink-row-offers-a-cautionary-tale-on-role-of-private-space-industry-in-wars%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%