%20One%20Mind%20at%20Work%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20as%20discussions%20of%20mental%20health%20at%20work%20grow%2C%20young%20people%20are%20struggling%20to%20distinguish%20between%20normal%20emotions%20and%20mental%20illness.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%20being%20open%20about%20mental%20health%20issues%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bwatershed%20moment%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20workplace%20and%20sparking%20meaningful%20change%20in%20the%20long%20term%2C%20according%20to%20Pike.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20in%20the%20effort%20to%20talk%20about%20mental%20health%20and%20share%20around%20mental%20illness%2C%20there%20can%20also%20become%20an%20expanded%20discourse%20of%20experience%20that%20at%20times%20loses%20track%20of%20normal%20fluctuation%20of%20human%20experience%20and%20mental%20illness%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFeeling%20stressed%20out%20when%20you%20have%20a%20deadline%20or%20feeling%20sad%2C%20disappointed%20or%20anxious%20are%20%26quot%3Bnormal%20life%20experiences.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20should%20all%20feel%20stressed%20sometimes%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20explaining%20that%20it%20helps%20people%20to%20cognitively%20focus%20and%20complete%20tasks.%20Meanwhile%2C%20anxiety%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Buseful%20cue%26quot%3B%20that%20can%20help%20you%20identify%20something%20wrong%20in%20your%20surroundings.%20But%20these%20feelings%20are%20not%20always%20indicators%20of%20serious%20mental%20illness.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20of%20that%20distinction%20can%20get%20lost%2C%26quot%3B%20Pike%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20I%20think%20social%20change%20usually%20happens%20in%20a%20way%20where%20we%20overcorrect%20or%20the%20pendulum%20swings%20way%20out%2C%20and%20then%20it%20comes%20back%20and%20settles%20in%20a%20place%20that%20is%20in%20a%20more%20integrated%20space.%20And%20I%20think%20that's%20what%20we're%20witnessing.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-feel-stressed-anxious-at-work-deloitte-survey-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EA%202023%20Deloitte%20survey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%2014%2C483%20Gen%20Zers%20from%2044%20countries%20found%20that%2046%25%20felt%20anxious%20and%20stressed%20out%20at%20work%20all%20or%20most%20of%20the%20time.%20Over%20a%20third%20said%20they%20were%20exhausted%2C%20lacked%20energy%2C%20and%20felt%20mentally%20distant%20from%20their%20job%20due%20to%20negativity%20or%20cynicism.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20some%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20seeking%20out%20alternatives%20to%20the%209-to-5%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flazy-girl-jobs-trend-gen-z-nyu-professor-suzy-welch-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%26quot%3Blazy%20girl%20jobs%26quot%3B%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20roles%20that%20are%20low-stress%20but%20offer%20good%20pay.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flazy-girl-jobs-trend-gen-z-nyu-professor-suzy-welch-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESuzy%20Welch%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20NYU%20business%20professor%2C%20previously%20said%20the%20trend%20is%20fuelled%20by%20Gen%20Z's%20%26quot%3Bstrong%20desire%20to%20avoid%20anxiety%20at%20any%20cost%26quot%3B%20because%20they%20haven%E2%80%99t%20made%20hard%20decisions%20or%20done%20hard%20things.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPike%20believes%20the%20discussions%20around%20mental%20health%20and%20mental%20illness%20must%20continue%20and%20that%20Gen%20Z%20will%20eventually%20learn%20to%20cope%20with%20difficult%20feelings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20may%20be%20times%20where%20a%20Gen%20Z%20young%20professional%20may%20have%20a%20threshold%20around%20stress%20or%20anxiety%20or%20mood%20that%20actually%20over%20time%20an%20expanded%20comfort%20with%20a%20wider%20range%20of%20emotional%20experience%20will%20actually%20be%20a%20maturing%20experience%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuccess%20grows%20out%20of%20learning%20how%20to%20get%20back%20on%20the%20horse%2C%20learning%20how%20to%20build%20the%20skills%2C%20how%20to%20ask%20for%20help%2C%20and%20how%20to%20build%20capacity%20in%20ways%20that%20didn't%20exist.%20That's%20part%20of%20maturing%20in%20the%20workplace.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-stress-anxiety-normal-life-experiences-expert-says-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708089704000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cf4bf36fcb546d2d5084d7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-stress-anxiety-normal-life-experiences-expert-says-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Feeling%20stressed%20and%20anxious%20can%20be%20a%20good%20thing.%20They%20can%20help%20you%20focus%20and%20complete%20tasks%2C%20a%20prominent%20psychologist%20says.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sbhaimiya%40insider.com%20(Sawdah%20Bhaimiya)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-stress-anxiety-normal-life-experiences-expert-says-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Variety%20Promotes%20Todd%20Spangler%20to%20Business%20Editor%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708089574000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FTodd-Spangler-Headshot-Dec-2023.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235913383%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Variety%20veteran%20Todd%20Spangler%20has%20been%20promoted%20to%20Business%20Editor%2C%20overseeing%20coverage%20of%20corporate%20and%20financial%20news%2C%20mergers%20and%20acquisitions%20and%20other%20deal%20activity%20for%20media%20and%20entertainment%E2%80%99s