r%20opposition%20leaders%20of%20the%20past.%20He%20was%20able%20to%20strike%20Putin%20in%20his%20sore%20spots%2C%20by%20making%20embarrassing%20revelations%20and%20by%20using%20his%20%E2%80%9Csmart%20voting%E2%80%9D%20strategy%2C%20with%20which%20he%20tried%20to%20deprive%20the%20president%E2%80%99s%20United%20Russia%20party%20of%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kremlin%20also%20struggled%20to%20contain%20the%20protests%20that%20he%20organized%2C%20which%20attracted%20tens%20of%20thousands%2C%20sometimes%20more%2C%20out%20onto%20the%20streets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENovichok%20poisoning%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20year%202020%20marked%20a%20drastic%20turning%20point%20for%20Navalny.%20It%20was%20the%20year%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fgermanys-scholz-praises-navalny-on-poisoning-anniversary%2Fa-62876296%5C%22%3Esurvived%20being%20poisoned%20with%20the%20nerve%20agent%20Novichok.%3C%2Fa%3E%20After%20receiving%20lifesaving%20treatment%20in%20Germany%2C%20he%20accused%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20Federal%20Security%20Service%2C%20the%20FSB%2C%20and%20Putin%20personally%2C%20of%20attempting%20to%20murder%20him.%20Despite%20the%20risks%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20return%20to%20Russia%20when%20he%20had%20recovered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20arrested%20immediately%20and%20sentenced%20to%20jail.%20This%20provoked%20an%20international%20outcry%20and%20some%20observers%20even%20likened%20the%20anti-corruption%20activist%20to%20%E2%80%9Ca%20Russian%20Nelson%20Mandela.%E2%80%9D%20Others%20saw%20him%20more%20like%20a%20knight%20from%20a%20Russian%20fairy%20tale%2C%20intrepid%20and%20willing%20to%20sacrifice%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20December%2C%20Navalny%20disappeared%20for%20several%20weeks.%20It%20was%20later%20discovered%20that%20he%20had%20been%20transferred%20to%20the%20penal%20camp%20in%20the%20far%20north%20of%20Siberia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%20believed%20that%20Russian%20authorities%20wanted%20to%20isolate%20him%20even%20further%20ahead%20of%20presidential%20elections%20in%20March.%20Previously%2C%20he%20had%20lodged%20a%20series%20of%20complaints%20against%20the%20ongoing%20violation%20of%20his%20rights%20as%20prisoner.%20To%20the%20end%2C%20he%20used%20his%20court%20appearances%20to%20voice%20biting%20criticism%20of%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20authoritarian%20rule%20and%20Moscow%E2%80%99s%20warn%20on%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20Navalny%20was%20no%20longer%20allowed%20to%20be%20present%20in%20court%20even%20on%20video.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEarly%20life%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%20was%20born%20near%20Moscow%20in%201976.%20His%20father%20was%20an%20army%20officer%20and%20his%20mother%20was%20a%20businesswoman.%20He%20went%20on%20to%20study%20law%2C%20securities%20and%20exchanges%20and%20became%20a%20lawyer%20and%20businessman.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%20got%20involved%20in%20politics%20in%20his%20mid-20s%2C%20joining%20the%20left-liberal%20Yabloko%20party%2C%20from%20which%20he%20was%20expelled%20in%202007%20over%20his%20nationalist%20tendencies%20and%20a%20spat%20with%20the%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20at%20this%20time%20that%20he%20made%20his%20most%20controversial%20statements%2C%20which%20cost%20him%20the%20sympathy%20of%20many%20others%20in%20the%20opposition%20and%20would%20dog%20him%20to%20the%20end.%20He%20joined%20the%20far-right%20NAROD%20movement%20(The%20People)%20and%20got%20involved%20with%20the%20Russian%20March%2C%20which%20brings%20together%20nationalist%20forces%20in%20the%20country%20and%20is%20notorious%20for%20its%20anti-immigrant%20stance%20and%20racist%20attitudes%20towards%20people%20from%20the%20Caucasus%20in%20particular.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny%20tried%20to%20distance%20himself%20from%20his%20earlier%20statements%20and%20apologized%20for%20derogatory%20comments%20about%20Georgians%2C%20which%20he%20had%20called%20%E2%80%9Crodents.%E2%80%9D%20But%20his%20apologies%20were%20not%20wholly%20convincing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnti-corruption%20campaigner%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20controversial%20for%20other%20reasons%2C%20too.%20His%20tendency%20toward%20self-promotion%20and%20what%20appeared%20at%20times%20to%20be%20arrogance%20toward%20journalists%20made%20it%20difficult%20for%20some%20to%20accept%20him%20as%20a%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20long%20time%2C%20his%20politics%20remained%20very%20vague.%20He%20drifted%20to%20the%20left%20when%20he%20promised%20a%20higher%20minimum%20wage%20and%20higher%20spending%20on%20health%20and%20education.%20However%2C%20his%20real%20passion%20was%20the%20fight%20against%20corruption%2C%20a%20subject%20that%2C%20according%20to%20various%20polls%2C%20Russians%20feel%20strongly%20about.%20He%20made%20a%20name%20for%20himself%20as%20a%20blogger%2C%20making%20revelations%20online%20that%20drew%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%2C%20later%20millions%2C%20of%20subscribers%20and%20amassed%20no%20end%20of%20powerful%20enemies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20work%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20his%20Anti-Corruption%20Foundation%20(FBK)%2C%20a%20media%20outlet%20that%20produced%20sophisticated%20documentaries%20investigating%20and%20exposing%20corruption%20among%20the%20Russian%20elite.%20In%20early%202021%2C%20within%20two%20weeks%20of%20being%20posted%20online%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fnavalny-team-releases-investigation-into-putins-palace%2Fa-56278956%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CPutin%E2%80%99s%20Palace%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20a%20huge%20luxury%20residence%20on%20the%20Black%20Sea%20believed%20to%20have%20been%20built%20for%20the%20Russian%20president%2C%20had%20exceeded%20100%20million%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20modern%20politician%2C%20Navalny%20was%20extremely%20adept%20at%20using%20social%20media.%20He%20would%20post%20a%20selfie%20of%20himself%20jogging%20on%20Instagram%20or%20a%20picture%20of%20himself%20with%20his%20wife%20and%20children%20on%20Facebook.%20His%20primary%20focus%20on%20the%20social%20networks%20arose%20from%20necessity%3A%20He%20did%20not%20have%20access%20to%20mainstream%20media%20outlets%20in%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20one%20exception%2C%20Navalny%20was%20not%20able%20to%20enter%20politics%20through%20legal%20means%20and%20his%20party%20was%20not%20registered.%20In%202013%2C%20he%20ran%20in%20Moscow%E2%80%99s%20mayoral%20election%2C%20garnering%20almost%20a%20third%20of%20the%20votes%20and%20coming%20second.%20Afterwards%2C%20the%20Kremlin%20did%20everything%20it%20could%20to%20keep%20him%20out%20of%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESubtle%20sense%20of%20humour%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20aspect%20of%20Navalny%E2%80%99s%20character%20that%20stood%20out%20was%20his%20subtle%20sense%20of%20humor.%20His%20first%20Instagram%20post%20after%20being%20poisoned%20was%3A%20%E2%80%9CHi%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20Navalny.%20I%20miss%20you.%E2%80%9D%20He%20went%20on%20to%20explain%20that%20he%20was%20able%20to%20breathe%20on%20his%20own%20completely%2C%20joking%20that%20this%20was%20an%20incredible%20process%20that%20many%20underestimated.%20%E2%80%9CI%20recommend%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20made%20jokes%20in%20all%20of%20his%20videos%20and%20even%20in%20the%20courtroom%2C%20having%20understood%20early%20on%20that%20it%20would%20be%20easier%20to%20get%20young%20people%20on%20board%20with%20humor%20rather%20than%20dry%20political%20analysis.%20His%20call%20to%20an%20FSB%20agent%20whom%20he%20suspected%20of%20poisoning%20him%2C%20which%20included%20details%20of%20removing%20traces%20of%20the%20nerve%20agent%20on%20his%20underpants%2C%20was%20worthy%20of%20an%20Oscar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20by%20targeting%20a%20younger%20audience%2C%20Navalny%20alienated%20a%20large%20part%20of%20the%20Russian%20population.%20His%20fans%20belonged%20to%20the%20well-educated%20urban%20middle%20class%2C%20a%20minority.%20He%20was%20not%20able%20to%20reach%20large%20swathes%20of%20the%20older%20population%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20believed%20the%20state%20propaganda%20depicting%20him%20as%20a%20criminal%20and%20puppet%20of%20the%20West.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20death%20marks%20a%20new%20chapter%20in%20Russian%20history.%20The%20country%20has%20lost%20its%20strongest%20opposition%20figure%2C%20one%20who%20was%20able%20to%20show%20that%20it%20is%20possible%20to%20stand%20up%20to%20the%20Kremlin%2C%20even%20from%20jail.%20But%20the%20destiny%20of%20Mandela%2C%20who%20went%20on%20to%20be%20his%20country%E2%80%99s%20president%20after%20his%20release%2C%20has%20been%20denied%20to%20Navalny.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fobituary-russian-activist-alexei-navalny-dead-at-47%2Fa-68275055%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20DW.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708089167000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12124701%2FEffect-26.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Frussian-activist-alexei-navalny-dies-in-prison%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russian%20opposition%20leader%20Alexei%20Navalny%20fought%20a%20lifelong%20crusade%20to%20drive%20Vladimir%20Putin%20from%20the%20Kremlin.%20His%20campaign%20seemed%20doomed%20from%20the%20start%2C%20but%20he%20got%20closer%20than%20many%20activists%20before%20him.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Frussian-activist-alexei-navalny-dies-in-prison%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Prince%20Harry%2C%20Meghan%20Adopt%20Sussex%20As%20Surname%20For%20Children.%20Here's%20Why%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EPrince%20Harry%20and%20Meghan%20Markle%2C%20the%20Duke%20and%20Duchess%20of%20Sussex%20have%20adopted%20the%20Sussex%20title%20as%20their%20children's%20last%20name%2C%20as%20per%20a%20report%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thetimes.co.uk%2Farticle%2Fprince-harry-meghan-sussex-archie-lilibet-children-name-royal-title-cnvf7d9jf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%20UK%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Their%20two%20children%20will%20now%20be%20referred%20to%20as%20Prince%20Archie%20Sussex%20and%20Princess%20Lilibet%20Sussex%2C%20instead%20of%20the%20Mountbatten-Windsors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20outlet%2C%20Prince%20Harry%20was%20called%20Captain%20Wales%20when%20he%20was%20in%20the%20British%20Army%2C%20thus%20it%20is%20thought%20that%20Sussex%20has%20been%20modified%20for%20each%20of%20their%20kids%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20development%20comes%20as%20the%20couple%20rebranded%20their%20website%20to%20%26quot%3Bunify%26quot%3B%20their%20family.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsussex.com%2F%5C%22%3Ewebsite%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20earlier%20called%20Archwell%2C%20has%20the%20latest%20news%20about%20the%20couple%2C%20bios%20for%20Harry%20and%20Meghan%20as%20well%20as%20links%20to%20their%20Archewell%20Foundation%20organization%20and%20Archewell%20Productions%20hub.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bios%20refer%20to%20their%20two%20kids%20as%20%26quot%3BPrince%20Archie%20and%20Princess%20Lilibet%26quot%3B%20despite%20Harry%20and%20Meghan%20stepping%20down%20as%20senior%20members%20of%20the%20royal%20family%20in%202020.%20According%20to%20the%20statements%20issued%20by%20The%20Office%20of%20Prince%20Harry%20%26amp%3B%20Meghan%2C%20The%20Duke%20%26amp%3B%20Duchess%20of%20Sussex%2C%20the%20couple%20aims%20to%20showcase%20their%20passions%20and%20endeavours%2C%20asserting%20their%20identities%20beyond%20traditional%20royal%20responsibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reality%20behind%20the%20new%20site%20is%20very%20simple%20-%20it's%20a%20hub%20for%20the%20work%20the%20Sussexes%20do%20and%20it%20reflects%20the%20fact%20the%20family%20have%2C%20since%20the%20King's%20coronation%2C%20the%20same%20surname%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20That's%20a%20big%20deal%20for%20any%20family.%20It%20represents%20their%20unification%20and%20it's%20a%20proud%20moment%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20insider%20told%20the%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20couple%20was%20slammed%20for%20using%20their%20royal%20titles%20and%20the%20Royal%20Coat%20of%20Arms%20on%20their%20new%20Sussex.com%20website.%20According%20to%20a%20royal%20insider%20who%20spoke%20to%20the%20outlet%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20isn't%20any%20sort%20of%20problem%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20royal%20family.%20It%20hasn't%20even%20been%20part%20of%20a%20conversation.%20Harry%20is%20more%20concerned%20about%20the%20health%20and%20wellbeing%20of%20the%20King%20and%20Kate%20and%20thinks%20that%20is%20where%20the%20focus%20should%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20certainly%20hasn't%20been%20any%20problem%20raised%20about%20the%20use%20of%20a%20coat%20of%20arms%20by%20anyone%20at%20the%20royal%20household%20-%20why%20would%20they%20object%20when%20it's%20perfectly%20normal%20and%20is%20pretty%20routine%3F%20Lots%20of%20people%20are%20familiar%20with%20the%20Duchy%20of%20Cornwall%20products%20in%20the%20shops%20and%20there%20are%20about%20800%20companies%20using%20the%20royal%20warrant%20coat%20of%20arms%20for%20commercial%20reasons.%20There's%20no%20use%20of%20the%20word%20'royal'%20on%20the%20site%20for%20a%20good%20reason%20-%20to%20ensure%20there%20could%20be%20no%20conflict%20with%20anyone's%20wishes.%26quot%3B%20they%20added.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708088700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2F2qd1gnc8_harry-meghan_625x300_16_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fprince-harry-meghan-markle-adopt-sussex-as-surname-for-children-amid-website-backlash-5070235%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Their%20two%20children%20will%20now%20be%20referred%20to%20as%20Prince%20