0been%20in%20jail%20since%20February%202021%20-%20since%20recovering%20from%20an%20assassination%20attempt%20the%20year%20before.%20He%20was%20poisoned%20with%20a%20nerve%20agent%20in%20August%202020%20while%20on%20a%20flight%20to%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20to%20be%20evacuated%20from%20a%20Russian%20hospital%20to%20one%20in%20Berlin%20for%20his%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20his%20recovery%20five%20months%20later%2C%20Mr%20Navalny%20returned%20to%20Russia%2C%20and%20was%20promptly%20arrested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20sent%20to%20jail%20for%20two-and-a-half%20years.%20Russian%20courts%20said%20he%20had%20violated%20the%20terms%20of%20a%202014%20suspended%20sentence%3B%20authorities%20accused%20him%20of%20failing%20to%20report%20to%20them%20regularly%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20legal%20team%20pointed%20out%20the%20claim%20was%20ridiculous%20since%20Mr%20Navalny%20spent%20the%20year%20in%20Germany%2C%20recovering%20from%20the%20attempt%20on%20his%20life.%20He%20was%20also%20in%20a%20coma%20during%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202014%20sentence%20was%20for%20allegations%20of%20embezzlement%20from%20a%20Russian%20subsidiary%20of%20a%20French%20cosmetics%20firm.%20The%20conviction%20was%20criticised%20by%20the%20European%20Court%20of%20Human%20Rights%20-%20which%20said%20the%20Russian%20government%20had%20to%20pay%20compensation%20-%20but%20was%20upheld%20by%20the%20Russian%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20sent%20to%20a%20penal%20colony%20in%20central%20Russia's%20Vladimir%20region%2C%20which%20is%20230km%20east%20of%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202022%20the%20sentence%20was%20increased%20by%20nine%20years%2C%20and%20he%20was%20moved%20to%20a%20new%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20in%20August%20last%20year%2C%20he%20received%20the%2019-year%20term%20for%20forming%20and%20funding%20extremist%20organisations%20and%20activities.%20That%20was%20months%20before%20Mr%20Putin%20began%20his%20re-