s%2C%20for%20whom%20farmers%20are%20demanding%20MSP%20be%20made%20legally%20binding%2C%20only%20constitute%2027.8%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20total%20agricultural%20produce.%20He%20added%20that%20the%20MSP%20regime%20for%20wheat%20and%20rice%20applies%20to%20some%20six%20or%20seven%20states%2C%20of%20which%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Telangana%20and%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20are%20new%20entries%2C%20and%20largely%20excludes%20most%20of%20east%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%2040-minute%20interview%20to%20Karan%20Thapar%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20professor%20Gulati%2C%20who%20is%20the%20Infosys%20Professor%20for%20Agriculture%20at%20ICRIER%20and%20former%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Commission%20for%20Agricultural%20Costs%20and%20Prices%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20high-flying%20sectors%20of%20Indian%20agriculture%2C%20such%20as%20poultry%2C%20which%20is%20growing%20at%208-9%25%2C%20fisheries%20at%207-8%25%2C%20and%20milk%20at%205-6%25%2C%20do%20not%20depend%20upon%20any%20MSP%20regime%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20spoke%20about%20how%20to%20improve%20the%20income%20of%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20believes%20making%20MSP%20legally%20binding%20would%20be%20anti-farmer.%20He%20also%20spoke%20about%20the%20ramifications%20and%20consequences%20of%20calculating%20MSP%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20Swaminathan%20formula%20of%20C2%20%2B%2050%25.%20It%20will%20increase%20food%20prices%20by%2025-30%25%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20discussed%20how%20farmers%20should%20be%20supported%2C%20either%20through%20some%20form%20of%20a%20price%20stabilisation%20fund%2C%20so%20that%20when%20market%20prices%20fall%20below%20the%20MSP%20levels%2C%20the%20government%20makes%20up%20the%20difference%2C%20or%20preferably%2C%20through%20an%20income%20support%20scheme%2C%20which%20is%20the%20practice%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20importantly%2C%20he%20explained%20how%20the%20real%20incomes%20of%20farmers%20can%20be%20improved.%20At%20present%2C%20the%20incomes%20are%20only%20modestly%20increasing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20spoke%20about%20incentivising%20farmers%20to%20shift%20from%20wheat%20and%20rice%20to%20high-value%20agricultural%20produce%2C%20such%20as%20fruits%2C%20vegetables%2C%20livestock%20and%20fisheries.%20He%20also%20spoke%20about%20not%20imposing%20arbitrary%20export%20controls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20explained%20the%20need%20for%20the%20government%20to%20move%20away%20from%20its%20pro-consumer%20bias%2C%20where%20they%20protect%20non-agricultural%20households%20against%20inflation%2C%20and%20create%20a%20level%20playing%20field%20which%20is%20more%20equal%20in%20handling%20farmer%20interests%20as%20well%20as%20consumer%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20addressed%20the%20trust%20deficit%20that%20has%20emerged%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years%20between%20the%20government%20and%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FiIwcv7walvY%3Fsi%3Da0AkvvagASBgiFmV%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708079791000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F16160448%2FKT-16-B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-msp-applies-to-only-10-of-agri-households-hike-will-raise-food-inflation-by-25-30%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20an%20interview%20to%20Karan%20Thapar%2C%20professor%20Ashok%20Gulati%20spoke%20about%20the%20ramifications%20and%20consequences%20of%20calculating%20MSP%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20Swaminathan%20formula%20of%20C2%2B50%25.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-msp-applies-to-only-10-of-agri-households-hike-will-raise-food-inflation