0suspended%20for%20allegedly%20displaying%20posters%20and%20participating%20in%20a%20discussion%20about%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20in%20Ayodhya%2C%20which%20university%20officials%20deemed%20a%20%E2%80%9Cviolation%20of%20the%20student%20code%20of%20conduct%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20university%20student%20disciplinary%20committee%20(USDC)%2C%20in%20its%20February%2010%20notice%20to%20one%20of%20the%20students%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CYou%20were%20allegedly%20involved%20in%20a%20serious%20violation%20of%20the%20student%20code%20of%20conduct.%20You%20were%20found%20to%20have%20been%20putting%20up%20posters%20and%20engaging%20in%20conversation%20that%20involved%20extremely%20derogatory%20and%20provocative%20words%20and%2For%20phrases%20aimed%20at%20detrimentally%20affecting%20the%20integrity%20and%20tranquility%20of%20the%20university%20space.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fdelhi%2Fjindal-university-suspends-two-students-for-ram-temple-discussion-putting-up-posters-9164206%2F%3Ftbref%3Dhp%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Anjoo%20Mohun%2C%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20Chief%20Communication%20Officer%2C%20stated%20that%20the%20students%20were%20suspended%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20guidelines%20for%20student%20conduct.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20suspended%20student%20argued%20that%20he%20was%20exercising%20his%20right%20to%20free%20speech%20in%20a%20democratic%20setup.%20The%20student%20acknowledged%20he%20was%20not%20a%20part%20of%20any%20student%20organisation%20that%20%E2%80%9Caligns%20with%20any%20specific%20political%20ideology%2C%20in%20particular%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20daily%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20poster%20of%20the%20public%20discussion%2C%20organised%20by%20the%20Revolutionary%20Student%20League%20on%20February%207%2C%20read%3A%20%E2%80%9CRam%20Mandir%3A%20A%20farcical%20project%20of%20Brahmanical%20Hindutva%20Fascism%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20student%20organisation%20claimed%20the%20discussion%20was%20interrupted%20by%20a%20section%20of%20students%20chanting%20slogans%20of%20%E2%80%98Jai%20Shri%20Ram%E2%80%99.%20In%20a%20post%20on%20Instagram%2C%20it%20called%20for%20the%20varsity%E2%80%99s%20student%20body%20to%20take%20the%20incident%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Csignal%20to%20join%20in%20against%20the%20struggle%20to%20claim%20back%20democratic%20political%20space%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708075856000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F16145108%2Fimage-1838.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fop-jindal-global-university-suspends-two-students-over-ram-mandir-discussion%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'You%20were%20found%20to%20have%20been%20putting%20up%20posters%20and%20engaging%20in%20conversation%20that%20involved%20extremely%20derogatory%20and%20provocative%20words...aimed%20at%20affecting%20the%20integrity%20and%20tranquility%20of%20the%20university%20space%2C'%20the%20university%20said%20in%20a%20notice%20to%20one%20of%20the%20students.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fop-jindal-global-university-suspends-two-students-over-ram-mandir-discussion%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%20%7C%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Was%20a%20Scheme%20to%20Strangle%20Democracy%20With%3A%20Kapil%20Sibal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F16145903%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-16-at-13.12.32.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20delivered%20its%20verdict%20on%20Thursday%2C%20February%2015%2C%20on%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme.%20A%20five-member%20constitution%20bench%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20had%20reserved%20its%20verdict%20in%20November%20last%20year%2C%20which%20was%20delivered%20by%20the%20court%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20stated%20that%20anonymous%20electoral%20bonds%20are%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20Article%2019(1)(A).%20Additionally%2C%20the%20court%20ruled%20that%20electoral%20bonds%20violate%20the%20right%20to%20information%2C%20asserting%20that%20voters%20in%20the%20country%20should%20have%20information%20about%20those%20who%20donate%20to%20political%20parties.%20It%20is%20against%20the%20rules%20to%20withhold%20information%20about%20donors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20decision%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20lawyer%20Kapil%20Sibal%20remarked%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20decision%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20historical.%20According%20to%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%2C%20every%20citizen%20of%20India%20has%20the%20right%20to%20know%20who%20has%20donated%20to%20which%20political%20party%20and%20how%20much.%E2%80%9D%20Sibal%20further%20expressed%20concerns%20about%20the%20financial%20transparency%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%2C%20suggesting%20that%20if%20the%20opposition%20comes%20together%20and%20raises%20this%20issue%20and%20makes%20it%20a%20national%20campaign%2C%20the%20opposition%20may%20benefit%20from%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20introduced%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20in%20early%202018.%20Through%20this%20scheme%2C%20companies%20and%20individuals%20in%20India%20can%20make%20anonymous%20donations%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20spoke%20to%20social%20activist%20Anjali%20Bhardwaj%20on%20this%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20one%20donates%20to%20a%20political%20party%20without%20any%20reason.%20Whoever%20donates%20wants%20the%20political%20party%20to%20work%20for%20them.%20The%20common%20people%20need%20to%20know%20from%20whom%20and%20how%20much%20money%20the%20party%20is%20taking.%20But%20this%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%20was%20an%20attack%20on%20the%20right%20to%20information.%E2%80%99%20She%20further%20said%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20banned%20this%20scheme%20by%20declaring%20it%20unconstitutional.%20So%2C%20this%20is%20a%20victory%20for%20people%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20information.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FHmikikixouY%3Fsi%3DweMutou_B1crDKcA%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708075800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F16145903%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-16-at-13.12.32.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwatch-electoral-bonds-were-a-scheme-to-strangle-democracy-with-kapil-sibal%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'No%20one%20donates%20to%20a%20political%20party%20without%20any%20reason%2C'%20activist%20Anjali%20Bhardwaj%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwatch-electoral-bonds-were-a-scheme-to-strangle-democracy-with-kapil-sibal%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ping%20pong%20fight%20costs%20Klinsmann%20his%20job%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708075680000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F02%2F70x70%2Fskynews-klinsmann-south-korea_6457480.jpg%3F20240216095524%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fjurgen-klinsmann-sacked-as-south-korea-head-coach-after-pre-cup-bust-up-13072823%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Former%20German%20football%20star%20Jurgen%20Klinsmann%20has%20been%20fired%20as%20head%20coach%20of%20the%20South%20Korean%20national%20team%20after%20a%20table%20tennis%20bust-up%20was%20blamed%20for%20the%20side's%20sem