A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107748341%2Cimgsize-1543839.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fimran-khans-party-to-hold-protests-across-pakistan-tomorrow-against-alleged-poll-rigging%2Farticleshow%2F107748216.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107748216.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fimran-khans-party-to-hold-protests-across-pakistan-tomorrow-against-alleged-poll-rigging%2Farticleshow%2F107748216.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fimran-khans-party-to-hold-protests-across-pakistan-tomorrow-against-alleged-poll-rigging%2Famp_articleshow%2F107748216.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fimran-khans-party-to-hold-protests-across-pakistan-tomorrow-against-alleged-poll-rigging%2Famp_articleshow%2F107748216.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Election%20Commission%20Has%20No%20Comments%20on%20Landmark%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Verdict%3A%20How%20it%20Changed%20its%20Stance%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09195651%2FUntitled-design-10.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20landmark%20judgment%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Thursday%20declared%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20%E2%80%9Cunconstitutional%E2%80%9D%20and%20violative%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20and%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1218090%2F%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3EArticle%2019(1)(a)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20court%20has%20ordered%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20to%20release%20details%20of%20all%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20purchased%20and%20directed%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20to%20publish%20the%20information%20on%20its%20website%20by%20March%2013%2C%202024.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInterestingly%2C%20the%20ECI%20had%20expressed%20concerns%20related%20to%20the%20absence%20of%20%E2%80%9Ctransparency%20of%20donations%E2%80%9D%20in%20electoral%20bonds%20but%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Franjan-gogoi-electoral-bonds-supreme-court%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3Edidn%E2%80%99t%20want%20a%20stay%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20the%20scheme%20suggesting%20that%20it%20would%20mean%20going%20back%20to%20the%20era%20of%20unaccounted%20cash%20transfers%2C%20which%20would%20cause%20further%20damage.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EInitial%20discussions%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBefore%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%C2%A0%20brought%20the%20scheme%20in%202018%2C%20the%20ECI%20warned%20the%20government%20that%20electoral%20bonds%20would%20help%20political%20parties%20hide%20illegal%20donations%20from%20foreign%20sources%20and%20might%20even%20%E2%80%9Clead%20to%20increased%20use%20of%20black%20money%20for%20political%20funding%20through%20shell%20companies%2C%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20a%20report%C2%A0%20by%20the%20Reporter%E2%80%99s%20Collective%20published%20in%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Farchive%2Fin%2Fentry%2Felectoral-bonds-narendra-modi-election-commission-opposition-arun-jaitley_in_5dce3cd1e4b01f982eff5c62%5C%22%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHuffington%20Post%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20report%20underlined%20that%20the%20ECI%20wrote%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Law%20in%20this%20regard%20on%20May%2026%2C%202017.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20its%20letter%2C%20the%20ECI%20described%20the%20amendment%20in%20Section%2029C%20of%20the%20Representation%20of%20Peoples%20Act%201951(RPA)%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cretrograde%20step%20as%20far%20as%20transparency%20of%20donations%20is%20concerned%E2%80%9D%20since%20political%20parties%20did%20not%20have%20to%20report%20to%20the%20commission%20regarding%20the%20donations%20received%20through%20electoral%20bonds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFurther%2C%20it%20was%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20if%20contributions%20were%20not%20reported%20then%20it%20will%20not%20be%20possible%20to%20ascertain%20if%20political%20parties%20have%20taken%20donations%20from%20government%20companies%20and%20foreign%20sources%2C%20which%20is%20prohibited%20under%20Section%2029B%20of%20RPA.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ECI%20had%20also%20underlined%20that%20amendment%20to%20Section%20182%20of%20the%20Companies%20Act%20took%20away%20the%20restriction%20that%20contribution%20can%20be%20made%20only%20to%20the%20extent%20of%207.5%25%20of%20net%20average%20profit%20of%20three%20preceding%20financial%20years%2C%20enabling%20even%20newly%20incorporated%20companies%20to%20donate%20via%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Law%20forwarded%20the%20ECI%E2%80%99s%20letter%20to%20the%20Finance%20Ministry%2C%20the%20report%20underlined%20that%20the%20commission%E2%80%99s%20concerns%20were%20ignored%20and%20the%20then%20finance%20minister%20Arun%20Jaitley%20set%20up%20a%20meeting%20on%20July%2019%2C%202017%20with%20the%20RBI%20and%20ECI%20to%20%E2%80%9Cfinalise%20the%20structure%20of%20the%20bond%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFurther%2C%20the%20report%20also%20underlined%20that%20a%20separate%20meeting%20was%20held%20between%20government%20officials%20and%20the%20then%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20(CEC)%20Achal%20Kumar%20and%20two%20election%20commissioners%20(ECs)%20Om%20Prakash%20Rawat%20and%20Sunil%20Arora.%20In%20this%20meeting%20held%20on%20July%2028%2C%202017%20with%20the%20CEC%20and%20ECs%2C%20the%20government%20officials%20made%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfalse%20claim%E2%80%9D%20that%20companies%20would%20make%20accounting%20entries%20in%20their%20books%20when%20buying%20electoral%20bonds%20which%20will%20lead%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccomplete%20transparency%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhen%20ECI%20flagged%20concerns%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20CPI%20(M)%2C%20Congress%20leader%20Jaya%20Thakur%20and%20non-profit%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%20filed%20petitions%20in%202017%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20underlining%20that%20the%20anonymity%20associated%20with%20electoral%20bonds%20undermined%20transparency%20in%20political%20funding%20and%20encroached%20upon%20voters%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20information.%20The%20petitions%20challenged%20the%20provisions%20of%20Finance%20Act%202017%2C%20which%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20anonymous%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20lines%20with%20the%20letter%20written%20by%20the%20ECI%2C%20the%20constitutional%20body%20filed%20a%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Franjan-gogoi-electoral-bonds-supreme-court%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ecounter-affidavit%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20this%20case%20flagging%20its%20concerns%20that%20the%20amendments%20to%20the%20IT%20Act%2C%20Representation%20of%20Peoples%20Act%20(RPA)%2C%20and%20Companies%20Act%20introduced%20by%20the%20Finance%20Act%202017%20will%20have%20a%20%E2%80%9Cserious%20impact%20on%20transparency%20of%20political%20finance%2Ffunding%20of%20political%20parties.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Felectoral-bonds-worth-more-than-rs-570-crore-sold-in-january-alone-60-in-the-value-of-rs-1-crore%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3ERs%20570%20Crore%20of%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Sold%20in%20January%20Alone%2C%2094%25%20Amount%20in%20Rs%201%20Crore%20Denomination%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESharp%20U-turn%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20March%2026%2C%202021%20refused%20to%20stay%20the%20release%20of%20the%20fresh%20set%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20from%20April%201%2C%202021%20for%20the%20Assembly%20elections%20which%20were%20scheduled%20that%20year%20in%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Kerala%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Assam%20and%20Puducherry.%20The%20apex%20court%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Felectoral-bonds-supreme-court-assembly-elections-171763%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3Edismissed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20application%20filed%20by%20the%20NGO%20ADR%20seeking%20stay%20of%20the%20bonds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENotably%2C%20the%20ECI%20opposed%20the%20plea%20for%20a%20stay%20in%20this%20instance.%20Underlining%20that%20the%20ECI%20was%20not%20opposed%20to%20electoral%20bonds%20but%20wanted%20more%20transparency%2C%20the%20commission%E2%80%99s%20counsel%20Senior%20Advocate%20Rakesh%20Dwivedi%20told%20the%20court%20that%20the%20issue%20of%20transparency%20can%20be%20considered%20at%20the%20final%20argument%20stage%20and%20there%20should%20be%20no%20interim%20stay.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIts%20spokesperson%20said%20yesterday%20when%20asked%20by%20reporters%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20no%20comments%20to%20offer%20on%20SC%20verdict%20of%20today.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708069066000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09195651%2FUntitled-design-10.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felection-commission-has-no-comments-on-landmark-verdict-on-electoral-bonds-how-it-changed-its-stance%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22From%20calling%20it%20%E2%80%9Cretrograde%20step%E2%80%9D%20to%20backing%20the%20opaque%20funding%20instrument